Create a Python script that reads Guidewire incident data from incidents.csv.

Requirements:
- Use pandas
- Load all incidents
- Handle missing values
- Combine useful fields (incident id, short description, work notes, resolution notes) into a searchable text field
- Print total incident count
- Keep code modular for future embedding generation





Create a Python module that generates embeddings for incident records.

Requirements:
- Use sentence-transformers
- Model: BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5
- Generate one embedding per incident
- Store incident metadata along with embeddings
- Add logging and progress information
- Design for approximately 4000 incidents





Create a Python script to store incident embeddings in Qdrant.

Requirements:
- Use local Qdrant database
- Create collection named incidents
- Vector size should match embedding model output
- Store incident id, description, work notes and resolution notes as payload
- Support insert and update operations
- Add logging and error handling




Create a semantic search module for incident retrieval.

Requirements:
- Accept free text incident description
- Generate embedding using BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5
- Search Qdrant collection
- Return top K similar incidents
- Include similarity score and incident metadata
- Return results as JSON




Create a Streamlit application for semantic incident search.

Requirements:
- Text area for incident description
- Search button
- User configurable top K results
- Display incident id
- Display similarity score
- Display short description
- Expandable section for work notes and resolution notes
- Clean enterprise UI




Create an MCP compatible HTTP service exposing incident search capability.

Requirements:
- Use FastAPI
- Endpoint: /api/search
- Accept incident description and top_k
- Call semantic search module
- Return JSON response
- Keep retrieval logic separate from API layer





